column18: 01/31/2012: An explosive device detonated near government offices in Reykjavik city, Reykjavik North Constituency, Iceland. The explosive device was partially detonated by a robot meant to deactivate it. No group claimed responsibility for the incident.
column97: An explosive device consisting of a gasoline container, a percussion cap, and a battery were used in the attack.
column108: It is unknown if any property was damaged in this attack.
